      "question": "For a one-hot target label, what does cross-entropy loss reduce to?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "The sum of all predicted probabilities",
        "The negative log probability assigned to the correct class",
        "The Euclidean distance between logits",
        "The raw score of the highest-scoring wrong class"
      ],
      "answer_index": 1,
      "explanation": "With a one-hot target, only the correct class term remains, so cross entropy becomes the negative log probability that the model assigns to the true label.",
